4️⃣ Using CompletableFuture (Best Practice)
Return async result (non-blocking)
CompletableFuture<String> future =
    CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> fetchData());

Handle result
future.thenAccept(result -> {
    System.out.println(result);
});

Transform result
future.thenApply(data -> data.toUpperCase());


2️⃣ CompletableFuture (Modern & Powerful)
What it is

CompletableFuture is an enhanced Future that supports:

Non-blocking execution
Callbacks
Chaining
Composition
Exception handling
CompletableFuture
    .supplyAsync(() -> 10)
    .thenApply(v -> v * 2)
    .thenAccept(System.out::println);
